
## `for loop` Syntax
```bash
for VARIABLE in 1 2 3 4 5 .. N
do
    command1
    command2
    commandN
done
```
OR
```bash
for VARIABLE in file1 file2 file3
do
    command1 on $VARIABLE
    command2
    commandN
done
```
OR
```bash
for OUTPUT in $(Linux-Or-Unix-Command-Here)
do
    command1 on $OUTPUT
    command2 on $OUTPUT
    commandN
done
```

## Examples

### loop by count
```bash
#!/bin/bash
for i in 1 2 3 4 5
do
   echo "Welcome $i times"
done
```



